description.narrative: Around 10 million children are targeted in polio immunization campaigns. In 2020, one NID and one SNID took place. Over 8 million caregivers in polio risk areas have been mobilised towards vaccine uptake. The vaccine refusal rate is 1.2 per cent (national level). The Polio campaigns stopped due to COVID-19. | Status:Constrained | As-of Date:30/07/2020
